<div id="review_183522388" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/183522388" />
    <a title="Maria" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1879634-maria"><img alt="Maria" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1262397494p2/1879634.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/183522388?book_show_action=true">Jul 09, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Maria" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Maria" href="/user/show/1879634-maria">Maria</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer183522388" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7828740769292834111">With the help of drawings, photos, cartoons, tables, diagrams &amp; notes, an emphasis on extremely lucid step-by-step explanations, examples, iteration &amp; reiteration &amp; plenty of humor, R Dawkins shows that we are indeed so lucky to be witness to the Greatest Show on Earth -- this wonderful book is addressed not only to those interested in our natural world (and who&apos;ll maybe wish they&apos;d majored in biology) but more particularly to the creationists and proponents of &quot;intelligent design&quot; -- as evidenc</span>
  <span id="freeText7828740769292834111" style="display:none">With the help of drawings, photos, cartoons, tables, diagrams &amp; notes, an emphasis on extremely lucid step-by-step explanations, examples, iteration &amp; reiteration &amp; plenty of humor, R Dawkins shows that we are indeed so lucky to be witness to the Greatest Show on Earth -- this wonderful book is addressed not only to those interested in our natural world (and who'll maybe wish they'd majored in biology) but more particularly to the creationists and proponents of "intelligent design" -- as evidence for evolution it's one of the most fascinating books I've ever read. It's a beautifully detailed and concisely written effort (albeit a bit repetitious at times) that's full of extraordinary facts both serious and silly, a real experience. It's TERRIBLY witty. It filled me with joy. It should be read by everyone everywhere. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7828740769292834111" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
