        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer80115216" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15553443802936786913">What a wonderful book! I&apos;ve enjoyed several other books by Richard Dawkins, and this is his best. The chapter named &quot;History Written All Over Us&quot; could have been called, &quot;Unintelligent Design&quot;. It is just one of many arguments, why evolution is a proven theory. <br/><br/>Dawkins makes a point that a good scientific theory must be falsibiable. That means, that if certain evidence were ever collected, or observations made, then one must conclude that the theory is false. He describes how if fossils were eve</span>
  <span id="freeText15553443802936786913" style="display:none">What a wonderful book! I've enjoyed several other books by Richard Dawkins, and this is his best. The chapter named "History Written All Over Us" could have been called, "Unintelligent Design". It is just one of many arguments, why evolution is a proven theory. <br /><br />Dawkins makes a point that a good scientific theory must be falsibiable. That means, that if certain evidence were ever collected, or observations made, then one must conclude that the theory is false. He describes how if fossils were ever found in the wrong geological strata, one would immediately have to conclude that evolution is false. But although tons of fossils have been discovered all over the world, not a single one has ever been found in the wrong geological layer.</span>
