  <span id="freeText13455500978960449101" style="display:none">So, I admire Dawkins as both a scientist and a writer. His passion for science and the endless search for truth is infectious and his talent for writing magnificent prose is noteable.<br /><br />I had the pleasure to go see him speak at the Center for Inquiry in D.C., and also got to mingle with him before the show (a fun story for sure). Needless to say, he was amazing. <br /><br />I know some people think he is an angry atheist, but I think they are missing the point, and he does a great job of making his point at the beginning of this book. <br /><br />A very worthwhile read for anyone curious about evolution. So much information yet very readable.</span>
